----------------------------------------------------------------------
Third-Party Dependencies
----------------------------------------------------------------------

CAI builds on top of many open-source projects. See `pyproject.toml`
for the authoritative dependency list. Notable runtime dependencies
and their licenses:

  - FastAPI                  (MIT)
  - Pydantic / Pydantic-Settings (MIT)
  - SQLModel / SQLAlchemy    (MIT)
  - litellm                  (MIT)
  - httpx                    (BSD-3-Clause)
  - structlog                (Apache-2.0 / MIT)
  - arq                      (MIT)
  - Jinja2                   (BSD-3-Clause)
  - Typer / Rich             (MIT)
  - python-libnmap           (Apache-2.0)
  - zaproxy (python client)  (Apache-2.0)
  - PyGithub                 (LGPL-3.0)
  - shodan                   (MIT)
  - python-gvm               (GPL-3.0)
  - authlib                  (BSD-3-Clause)

Some optional integrations invoke external binaries (Nmap, Trivy,
Nuclei, Gitleaks, Trufflehog, dnstwist, Checkov, kube-bench, ZAP,
Greenbone) which are NOT redistributed by this project and remain
under their respective upstream licenses.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
Lab Targets (NOT redistributed)
----------------------------------------------------------------------

The `lab` Docker Compose profile references intentionally vulnerable
third-party applications (OWASP Juice Shop, DVWA, WebGoat). These
images are pulled at runtime from their official registries and are
not part of this distribution.
